'''《魔鬼必歌妙音耶？》'''（{{lang-en|''Must the Devil Have All the Good Tunes?''}}）是[[美国|美国]][[作曲家|作曲家]][[约翰·库利奇·亚当斯|约翰·库利奇·亚当斯]]所作的第三部[[钢琴协奏曲|钢琴协奏曲]]，其标题取自德意志[[神學家|神學家]][[马丁·路德|马丁·路德]]的一句名言。<ref>{{Cite web|title=John Adams Must The Devil Have All The Good Tunes|url=https://www.newyorker.com/goings-on-about-town/classical-music/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes|access-date=2020-08-13|website=The New Yorker|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200808102052/https://www.newyorker.com/goings-on-about-town/classical-music/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes|dead-url=no}}</ref>该作品由[[古斯塔沃·杜达梅尔|古斯塔沃·杜达梅尔]]于2019年3月7日指挥[[洛杉矶爱乐乐团|洛杉矶爱乐乐团]]同[[王羽佳|王羽佳]]首演，后于2019年的11月录制，并由[[德意志留聲機|德意志留聲機]]唱片公司于2020年4月17日发布。此前亚当斯已分别于1989年和1997年作钢琴协奏曲《{{link-en|厄洛斯的钢琴|Eros Piano}}》和《{{link-en|世纪摇滚|Century Rolls}}》。<ref>{{Cite web|last=Desk|first=BWW News|title=LA Phil and Gustavo Dudamel Release World Premiere Recording of John Adams “Must the Devil Have All the Good Tunes?”|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwclassical/article/LA-Phil-and-Gustavo-Dudamel-Release-World-Premiere-Recording-of-John-Adams-Must-the-Devil-Have-All-the-Good-Tunes-20200403|access-date=2020-08-13|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en}}</ref>

== 创作 ==
亚当斯将该作品标题的灵感归结于[[紐約客|紐約客]]杂志中的一篇关于[[多蘿西·戴伊|多蘿西·戴伊]]的文章其中的一段话，即“魔鬼必歌妙音耶？”，而此前亚当斯选定的是“哈利路亚的路口”（Hallelujah Junction）。该作品由三个传统形式的乐章组成，即符合钢琴协奏曲的快-慢-快格式，且乐章之间没有停歇。<ref>{{cite web |author1=Sarah Cahill |title=Must the Devil Have All the Good Tunes? (world premiere, LA Phil commission with generous support from the Lenore S. and Bernard A. Greenberg Fund) |url=https://www.laphil.com/musicdb/pieces/4789/must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-world-premiere-la-phil-commission-with-generous-support-from-the-lenore-s-and-bernard-a-greenberg-fund |website=LA Phil |accessdate=2021-03-20 |archive-date=2019-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004002223/https://www.laphil.com/musicdb/pieces/4789/must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-world-premiere-la-phil-commission-with-generous-support-from-the-lenore-s-and-bernard-a-greenberg-fund |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=== 结构 ===
该作品包含三个乐章：
{{ordered list |type=upper-roman
|粗犷的，时髦的，但节奏很快的；神经质的，机器人似的|慢得多；轻轻地，放松的|更快速的：痴迷的、摇摆的}}
演奏时长总计为28分钟。<ref>{{cite web |title=ADAMS Must The Devil Have All The Good Tunes? |url=https://www.deutschegrammophon.com/en/catalogue/products/adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-11931 |website=Deutsche Grammophon |accessdate=2021-03-20 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308143647/https://www.deutschegrammophon.com/en/catalogue/products/adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-11931 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

亚当斯一改之前在钢琴协奏曲《世纪摇滚》通过活泼且重复的极简主义节奏的开场风格，转而在该作品的第一乐章由钢琴奏出重复且强而有力的低音[[和弦|和弦]]开场，随后这样的[[乐想|乐想]]又逐渐转移至整个乐团。<ref>{{cite news |author1=Barbara Jepson |title=‘John Adams: Must the Devil Have All the Good Tunes?’ and ‘Shostakovich: Violin Concertos’ Reviews: A Form Fit for Virtuosos |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-and-shostakovich-violin-concertos-reviews-a-form-fit-for-virtuosos-11592252248 |accessdate=2021-03-20 |work=The Wall Street Journal |date=June 15, 2020 4:17 pm ET |archive-date=2020-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200811024204/https://www.wsj.com/articles/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-and-shostakovich-violin-concertos-reviews-a-form-fit-for-virtuosos-11592252248 |dead-url=no }}</ref>沉思般的第二乐章融合钢琴协奏曲的传统演奏风格以及粗犷和节奏强劲的元素，尽管在较慢的乐章，亚当斯依旧通过稳定持续的弦乐创造出潜在的紧张感。<ref>{{cite news |author1=RICHARD S. GINELL |title=Review: John Adams delivers a devil of a new concerto. Yuja Wang pounds it out |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-john-adams-devil-review-20190308-story.html |accessdate=2021-03-20 |work=LA Times |date=MARCH 8, 2019 12:40 PM PT |archive-date=2021-03-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210313003956/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-john-adams-devil-review-20190308-story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>伴随着爵士风的钢琴演奏以及咆哮般的低音，该作品在第三乐章被其悦耳而又简单的[[旋律|旋律]]和其即兴般的[[变奏|变奏]]推向了高潮。<ref>{{cite news |title=John Adams: Must the Devil Have All the Good Tunes? etc |url=https://www.classical-music.com/reviews/concerto/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-etc/ |accessdate=2021-03-20 |work=Classical-music |date=August 6, 2020 at 9:00 am |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126044818/https://www.classical-music.com/reviews/concerto/john-adams-must-the-devil-have-all-the-good-tunes-etc/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

